724478f.text:
854-56 West End Avenue, east side, adjoining S.E. corner of
102nd Street.
These two and the corner house, 858, were the first three houses to be erected in this block, and date back to the late 1880's. The adjoining small apartment house, 850-52, was built about
1900.
About 1910.
A closer view, taken simultaneously with the above.
About 1910.

724480f-a.text:
West End Avenue, east side, from 102nd to 1O3rd Streets, showing 860 to 878 West End Avenue. The last three brownstone houses, on the corner of 103rd Street, will be demolished late in 1922 for
an apartment building.
This is a typical summer photograph. Compare the winter photograph
of 862-64-66.
Probably June 1911.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

724479f-a.text:
West End Avenue, west side, at 102nd Street, showing the new 865 West End Avenue apartment house nearing completion. It replaces five old houses, three of which are shown in photographs about
191O.
The building shown in part on the S.W. corner ts The Standoche, typical of the earier [sic] type of apartment house on this avenue.
1925.
American Photo Service, Inc.
